{"TopicId":173254,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"Looking for a Navball texture changing mod","CreatedByName":"Lego_Prodigy","CreatedById":187421,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-30T15:51:44Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Lego_Prodigy","CreatedById":187421,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-30T15:51:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI find the default NavBall texture quite confusing, as it only reads north and it might be screwing with the success of my missions. Does anybody know of a good mod for navball textures? Im using the latest version of KSP, so keep that in mind. (on a small note, I would love a navball texture with green on black, with all 4 compass directions in green, but thats just a personal want).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Snark","CreatedById":125662,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-30T16:11:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMoving to Add-on Discussions.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"klesh","CreatedById":110814,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-30T16:28:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223339851\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022173254\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221522425104\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022187421\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Lego_Prodigy\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n29 minutes ago, Lego_Prodigy said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nquite confusing, as it only reads north\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHuh?\u00A0 It provides indications for all cardinal directions, indicated by degrees from North.\u00A0 You just need to learn how to make use of the information its providing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nN=0/360\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nE=90\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nS=180\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nW=270\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022zkPNw4k.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022316\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/zkPNw4k.png\u0022 width=\u0022395\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Lego_Prodigy","CreatedById":187421,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-30T16:34:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI also don\u0027t find that very helpful, as I often forget that kind of thing when Im flying. I can fly things very smoothly, but its things like the compass headings that screw me over.\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\nI went to a 3 day camp of a naval aviation place, and it was only on the last day that I actually found the compass.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"klesh","CreatedById":110814,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-30T17:15:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIts just remembering 4 numbers?\u00A0 You can do it. I believe in you.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-03-30T17:16:53Z\u0022 title=\u002203/30/2018 05:16  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 30, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by klesh\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DoctorDavinci","CreatedById":150019,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-30T18:21:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed4725568269\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/164158-13-navballtexturechanger-v16-8717/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:212px;max-width:500px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}